Jim Hughes (hughes@raistlan.network.com) wrote:
: I am looking for hardware chips that generate digital
: random number. I am NOT looking for PRN sequence
: generators. I am looking for digital noise sources.

: Please respond via email to
: 	hughes@network.com

: Thanks.

: jim

National semiconductor has/had a noise-source chip; it was a little 8-pin
DIP, and you could tell it to generate either white or pink noise - it was
intended for audio applications. 
Don't know if they're still available, but you might be able to accomplish
something similar with an open-input audio amp, and a little selective
feedback.

HTH

Dave Merriman
